  </FONT><FONT  COLOR="#400040" SIZE=4 PTSIZE=12><B><I><U>Background</FONT><FONT  COLOR="#000000" SIZE=2 PTSIZE=8></B></I></U><BR>
</P><P ALIGN=LEFT>  <BR>
</FONT><FONT  COLOR="#400040" SIZE=3 PTSIZE=10><B>Some people have luck. Some people dont. Simple fact of life. Justin does not. But this particular enemy of fate didnt take it well. He didnt become depressed. He didnt become optimistic about the "good things in life." And most of all.. he didnt get screwed up, at least not in the way they are on Loveline. This particular unlucky one took it out on others.<BR>
	Justin Lightman, a native of Oakland, California, was born to Phil and Lilly Lightman. His dad was a construction worker, alcoholic, wife-beater, avid believer in child abuse, devoted racist, and king jerk all rolled into one. Lilly was a victem of love. She'd long since lost affection for Phil, but knew if she left him, he'd come after her with a lead pipe. She was a good person, charitable, though she couldnt really afford to be, a pacifist, too. She wasnt very religeous, but it didnt seem to be a real character flaw for her.<BR>
	Justin got very little from his parents. He was a "B" student in school, though he was capable of As.  School just didn't work well with him. The teachers were sympathetic with the boy, having so many bruises all over. But they wrote it off from school yard fights. Something he was both fond of and good at. He spent so much time in the Principal's Office that he knew the guy on a first name basis. He ran in with a bad crowd, too. One thing he wouldnt do, though, was drugs. He felt it impared his ability to beat the crap out of people. He was a fair sized kid. Little scrawny when he was little, but he could hold his own. He could benchpress over 100 pounds at age 13. Not much more, and he could only do it 20 times.<BR>
	He had lots of girlfriends, mostly from the bad crowd, and he didnt do anything behind their backs. He didnt think he had to. He also got sick of his parents. His dad beat him, and his mom kept making empty promises. "It'll get better," she would say as she tended some open cuts his father's ring had made,"You just wait." But things never did get better. His dad had a nice handgun collection, too. He waited untill they were asleep, then he shot them both. With a bunch of friends to help him, he put a dead body of about his size in there, and burned the house down. This event happened at age 14.<BR>
	The firemen didnt get there in time. The bodies inside were completely destroyed. With his own fake death, he lived life out in the world.  First thing he did was head out of Oakland.<BR>
	He lived on the land. He'd get into brawls for cash, occasionally stealing. Lure a victem into an alley and... POW! Over the head with a trash can. He saved up some and bought guns on the black market. His two pistols, and his sniper rifle. First he bought a single pistol.. a year later, he bought another.. then he got himself his switchblade.. and finally, after being trained in there use by some old guy who wanted a student, he got his sniper rifle. Isnt the black market great? No serial numbers on anything. His "Mentor" Joe Winston, gave the kid three silencers. Looks like he wanted an assassin. Well, Justin liked the idea.. he liked it so much he put his silencers in and shot Joe between the eyes.<BR>
	Now, with a stolen Harley, 14 years after he killed his folks, he's on his way to Voletta. Why? Because.. it's just a sleepy little town. The perfect place to hide out, hone his skills...<BR>
